**Recommendation: Redis Streams** — definitive for a 6-person team with Redis already in production and no Kafka experience.

The decision hinges on three hard constraints that Kafka cannot meet:

| Constraint | Redis Streams | Apache Kafka |
|---|---|---|
| Production value in 2 weeks | ✅ Day-one prototype, week-one hardened | ❌ 3–4 weeks minimum + team learning curve |
| No dedicated infra engineer | ✅ Already operate Redis; one familiar system | ❌ 3+ brokers + ZK/KRaft; new operational surface |
| Modest budget | ✅ Zero new infra cost | ❌ Self-hosted = ops burden; managed = $300–1,200+/mo |

The exactly-once requirement for billing notifications is addressed via a consumer-side idempotency pattern (deduplication key with a PostgreSQL UNIQUE constraint) — a well-understood, auditable approach that keeps the guarantee at the application layer where we can test it directly, rather than relying on broker-level semantics.
